Telkom has launched a new 150MB FreeMe prepaid bundle, which is priced at R29. The bundle will be available from 1 June and was launched as part of the operator’s Z’Kipha More prepaid campaign. The FreeMe 150MB Bundle is available to all Telkom mobile subscribers as an ad-hoc purchase only, and provides users with: The bundle is valid for 14 days, after which the unused benefits will expire. Z’Kipha More also includes Telkom More, which allows customers to double their airtime when they recharge. “We’re extending FreeMe benefits even further with the 150MB FreeMe bundles for just R29,” said Telkom consumer managing executive Erna Korff.